race.comment: OUTCASTER (10) should be a big improver. Fitter for two runs back and is crying out for the extra ground. Comes back a notch and in this class is expected to improve sharply. THUNDER ZEUS (4) is also fitter for the two runs back, showing improvement second-up when out to 2000m. Fitter again and should feature with any luck from the wide draw. GLOBAL ECLIPSE (1) has placed at all three this time in and is bursting to win. The claim offsets the big weight a little and will give a sight.  LUMPYS HIGHWAY (5) is handy gelding who finished sixth last start but was beaten only 2.25 lengths over 2000m at Mornington. Won only try course and distance and expected to run well.
